					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think you should initialize registers $4000 and $4002. $4002 holds the 8 least significant bits of the pitch value, and $4000 determines whether or not it sweeps up, the volume, etc. I don't actually know much about hardware volume decay, because I do volume decay manually to have more control over it. I would just advise against assuming $4000 or $4002 have any value, so just initialize them.
<br />
<br />Also, it looks like your code is waiting for Vblank in an infinite loop. It would be best to put the code that's executed once every frame in the NMI routine, which is fired up every Vblank.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
